Package fr.lirmm.chocominer.app.specialized.algorithm.managers

Interface AlgorithmManagerInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractFrequentPatternsAlgorithmManager, FCIAlgorithmManager, FGAlgorithmManager, FIAlgorithmManager, MFIAlgorithmManager, MRIAlgorithmManager, PRIAlgorithmManager
public interface AlgorithmManagerInterface
An algorithm manager will, being true to its name, manage algorithms. As in, store SPMF algorithms that are compatible with its mining strategy. For example, to mine Frequent Closed Itemsets, one can use the LCM, Zart, AprioriClose, etc. algorithms. The FCIAlgorithmManager will store these names in a Map and allow for a facilitated access to the corresponding algorithm runner.
Author:
Theodore Picot
